The Zondo Commission will continue to hear evidence linked to the billion-rand Free State housing project. Former human settlements head of department, Gift Mokoena is expected to give evidence. JOHANNESBURG - The Zondo Commission continued to hear evidence linked to the billion-rand Free State housing project. Former human settlements head of department, Gift Mokoena was expected to give evidence. Between 2010 and 2011 over R1-billion was allocated to build low-cost housing units, but this did not happen. Another former Human Settlement head, Nthimotse Mokhesi says the contract was fraudulent.